# Gizmodo App - Privacy Policy

**Last Updated: November 2025**

## Introduction

Gizmodo ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our mobile application ("App").

## Information We Collect

### Data Collected by Our App

Our App collects the following types of data:

#### 1. Device ID
- **What we collect**: Device identifiers, including advertising identifiers (IDFA)
- **How we use it**: 
  - Third-Party Advertising: To display relevant advertisements through AdMob
  - Analytics: To measure ad performance and user engagement
  - App Functionality: For fraud prevention and security
- **Linked to User**: Yes
- **Used for Tracking**: Yes

#### 2. Product Interaction Data
- **What we collect**: Information about how you interact with the App, including ad views, clicks, taps, and app launches
- **How we use it**:
  - Third-Party Advertising: To optimize ad delivery and display relevant ads
  - Analytics: To understand user behavior and improve the App
- **Linked to User**: Yes
- **Used for Tracking**: Yes

#### 3. Advertising Data
- **What we collect**: Information about advertisements you see and interact with
- **How we use it**:
  - Third-Party Advertising: To display and optimize third-party advertisements
  - Analytics: To measure ad effectiveness and performance
- **Linked to User**: Yes
- **Used for Tracking**: Yes

#### 4. Crash Data
- **What we collect**: Crash logs and error reports
- **How we use it**:
  - Analytics: To understand app stability and identify issues
  - App Functionality: To improve app performance and minimize crashes
- **Linked to User**: Yes
- **Used for Tracking**: No

#### 5. Performance Data
- **What we collect**: App performance metrics, including launch time, energy use, and system performance
- **How we use it**:
  - Analytics: To evaluate app performance and user experience
  - App Functionality: To improve scalability, performance, and optimize the App
- **Linked to User**: Yes
- **Used for Tracking**: No

### Local Game Data

The App also stores game data locally on your device using local storage:
- Best score
- Top level reached
- Game progress

This local game data is **NOT** collected, transmitted, or shared with third parties. It remains on your device only.

## Third-Party Services

### Google AdMob

Our App uses Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob is a third-party advertising service provided by Google LLC.

**AdMob collects and uses:**
- Device identifiers (IDFA)
- Product interaction data
- Advertising data
- Crash and performance data (for analytics)

**AdMob's use of data:**
- To provide, maintain, and improve AdMob services
- To show you personalized ads
- To measure ad performance
- To prevent fraud and abuse

For more information about how Google uses data, please visit: [Google Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy)

**AdMob's data sharing:**
- AdMob may share data with advertisers and partners to deliver relevant ads
- Data may be shared with analytics providers
- Data may be used for advertising measurement across apps and websites

## Data Sharing

We share the following data with third parties:

### Third-Party Advertising Partners
- **Device ID**: Shared with AdMob and advertising partners for ad targeting
- **Product Interaction Data**: Shared for ad optimization and measurement
- **Advertising Data**: Shared for ad delivery and performance measurement

### Analytics Partners
- **Product Interaction Data**: Shared for analytics and user behavior analysis
- **Advertising Data**: Shared for ad performance measurement
- **Crash Data**: Shared for app stability analysis
- **Performance Data**: Shared for app performance optimization

## Your Rights and Choices

### Opt-Out of Personalized Ads

You can opt out of personalized advertising by adjusting your device settings:

**iOS Devices:**
1. Go to Settings → Privacy & Security → Apple Advertising
2. Turn off "Personalized Ads"

**Limit Ad Tracking:**
1. Go to Settings → Privacy & Security → Tracking
2. Turn off "Allow Apps to Request to Track"

### Data Access and Deletion

You have the right to:
- Request access to your personal data
- Request deletion of your personal data
- Object to processing of your personal data

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided in the "Contact Us" section below.

## Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.

## Children's Privacy

**This App is NOT made for children.** The App is designed for users 9 years and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately.

## International Users

If you are using the App from outside the United States, please be aware that your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States where our servers are located.

## Compliance

We comply with:
- General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
- Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)
- Apple App Store Guidelines

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.

